                <div class="aboutGameSection">
                    <h1>Does it worth your time?</h1>
                    <p class="indent">
                        Resident Evil 3 shares the same characteristics with the rest of the series in the third person
                        category. It is short, below average difficulty and includes a variety of ingame challenges to
                        keep it replayable and not feel boring. Completing the game will unlock the next difficulty
                        level, and that's why you need at least 3 playthroughs to unlock all the difficulty levels.
                    </p>
                    <p class="indent">
                        As you complete challenges you gain points that you can spend on the shop for items, like
                        weapons and different boosts. These will not disable achievements, and if you want to avoid
                        farming for points, do not buy anything until you are familiar with the game.
                    </p>
                    <p class="indent">
                        Those shop items are important for completing the most difficult achievements such as finishing
                        the game with S rank on the highest difficulty, or finish the game without ever opening the
                        item box.
                    </p>
                    <h2>First Playthrough</h2>
                    <p class="indent">
                        For your first playthrough play on standard difficulty. Just focus on learning the game,
                        practice the aim and dodge mechanics and make as many weapon kills as possible for the
                        challenges. If you want to farm for points, this is the playthrough to do it. You need all the
                        boosts, the hip pouches and the infinite rocket launcher for the inferno difficulty. Kill
                        Nemesis at least once at the first part of the game when he ambushes you for

                        <span class="achievement">
                            <%= achievements[8].displayName %>
                            <span class="tooltip-content"><img src=<%= achievements[8].icon %> alt="" />
                                <span class="tooltip-text">
                                    <%= achievements[8].description %>
                                </span>
                            </span>
                        </span>

                        and kill the zombie at the entrance of the police station with Carlos for

                        <span class="achievement">
                            <%= achievements[12].displayName %>
                            <span class="tooltip-content"><img src=<%= achievements[12].icon %> alt="" />
                                <span class="tooltip-text">
                                    <%= achievements[12].description %>
                                </span>
                            </span>
                        </span>.

                        A fair number of achievements will unlock naturally.

                        <span class="achievement">
                            <%= achievements[20].displayName %>
                            <span class="tooltip-content"><img src=<%= achievements[20].icon %> alt="" />
                                <span class="tooltip-text">
                                    <%= achievements[20].description %>
                                </span>
                            </span>
                        </span>

                        for defeating two enemies with one shot,

                        <span class="achievement">
                            <%= achievements[5].displayName %>
                            <span class="tooltip-content"><img src=<%= achievements[5].icon %> alt="" />
                                <span class="tooltip-text">
                                    <%= achievements[5].description %>
                                </span>
                            </span>
                        </span>

                        for crafting an item,

                        <span class="achievement">
                            <%= achievements[6].displayName %>
                            <span class="tooltip-content"><img src=<%= achievements[6].icon %> alt="" />
                                <span class="tooltip-text">
                                    <%= achievements[6].description %>
                                </span>
                            </span>
                        </span>

                        for improving a weapon,

                        <span class="achievement">
                            <%= achievements[7].displayName %>
                            <span class="tooltip-content"><img src=<%= achievements[7].icon %> alt="" />
                                <span class="tooltip-text">
                                    <%= achievements[7].description %>
                                </span>
                            </span>
                        </span>
                        for expanding your inventory and

                        <span class="achievement">
                            <%= achievements[19].displayName %>
                            <span class="tooltip-content"><img src=<%= achievements[19].icon %> alt="" />
                                <span class="tooltip-text">
                                    <%= achievements[19].description %>
                                </span>
                            </span>
                        </span>

                        for destroying a Charlie doll. Story related are:

                        <span class="achievement">
                            <%= achievements[0].displayName %>
                            <span class="tooltip-content"><img src=<%= achievements[0].icon %> alt="" />
                                <span class="tooltip-text">
                                    <%= achievements[0].description %>
                                </span>
                            </span>
                        </span>,
                        <span class="achievement">
                            <%= achievements[1].displayName %>
                            <span class="tooltip-content"><img src=<%= achievements[1].icon %> alt="" />
                                <span class="tooltip-text">
                                    <%= achievements[1].description %>
                                </span>
                            </span>
                        </span>,
                        <span class="achievement">
